Eight guards at Nauru detention centre have been suspended after they posted anti-Islamic messages on social media . 
  The men were pictured with Pauline Hanson at the Reclaim Australia rally in Brisbane . 
  Seven of the guards are former Australian Defence personnel . 
  The employees were found to be contravening a company policy that they display 'cultural sensitivity' One guard referred to asylum seekers as 'the enemy' The men are part of the emergency response team at the detention centre . 
 